Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes an integration solution for two networking protocols, FPMIPv6 and MIH, to optimize heterogeneous handover. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The proposed solution involves the use of agents to facilitate handover decision-making and management. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the performance analysis of the proposed solution under different scenarios, which involves the use of information theory concepts. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to the integration of FPMIPv6 and MIH. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - Unlikely, but the paper may involve the use of hardware components to implement the proposed solution.
